   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">Previewing a campaign is done using either of the following types:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Based on the data that are entered.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Using the Public Portal.</li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To preview a campaign based on the data that are entered, refer to <xref href="../Campaigning_for_Projects/Publishing_a_Campaign.dita"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Previewing a campaign using the Public Portal enables you to see how it appears to the general public.</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol> page, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">All Campaigns</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">All Campaigns</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Enter a project name in the search field to look for an appropriate project.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">All Projects</uicontrol> section, select an appropriate project to view all the details pertaining to that project.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Reference Documents</uicontrol> to view reference documents such as project design, project execution plan, and so on.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To verify the project's location in the map, zoom in the map. Select the appropriate project location in the map to view more details of the project.</cmd>
         </step>
